)", "w": "105715"}, {"t": "Lullabye (Goodnight, My Angel)", "w": "86995"}, {"t": "Fantasy", "w": "72696"}, {"t": "Summer, Highland Falls", "w": "26154"}, {"t": "Soliloquy", "w": "59267"}, {"t": "Somewhere Along the Line", "w": "121203"}, {"t": "Turn the Lights Back On", "w": "124630"}], "quotes": [], "about_quotes": [{"speaker": "Michael Weiss", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "I mean I think of in the 80s even Madison Square Garden, Giants Stadium, pop stars would fill — you know Billy Joel to Bruce Springsteen, Madonna, Prince, Michael Jackson, © Fillius Jazz Archive -2- whoever, would fill 50,000 seat stadiums regularly.", "doc_title": "Michael Weiss interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, December 22, 2021", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/michael-weiss-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-december-22-2021"}, {"speaker": "Mike Davis", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 1.0, "evidence": "you hear these great songwriters talk about it from Billy Joel to Sting to Carla Bley", "doc_title": "Mike Davis interviewed by Monk Rowe, via Zoom, April 1, 2024", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/mike-davis-interviewed-monk-rowe-zoom-april-1-2024"}, {"speaker": "Phil Woods", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "I heard my solo all over the world. In fact, my solo is in the piano music, you know. And I made a grand total of 300 dollars.", "doc_title": "Phil Woods — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://americanhistory.si.edu/sites/default/files/file-uploader/Phil%20Woods%20Interview%20Transcription%20%282%29.pdf"}, {"speaker": "Phil Woods", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.95, "evidence": "I did Phoebe Snow’s overdub and Billy Joel in the same day — the same half hour.", "doc_title": "Phil Woods interviewed by Monk Rowe, Delaware Water Gap, PA, November 8, 1999", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/phil-woods-interviewed-monk-rowe-delaware-water-gap-pa-november-8-1999"}, {"speaker": "Toots Thielemans", "relation": "collaborated with", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "You did some things with Billy Joel. So I’m not concerned with jazz. ... And that’s how I got the rehearsal… the call. And, oh, one funny thing. Yeah, you [inaudible]. And there was… Paul Simon... I’m exaggerating but his facial or his behavior doesn’t really react to the gravity of the event. [laug", "doc_title": "Toots Thielemans — Smithsonian Jazz Oral History", "collection": "si", "url": "https://americanhistory.si.edu/sites/default/files/file-uploader/Toots%20Thielemans%20Interview%20Transcription%20%282%29.pdf"}, {"speaker": "John Pizzarelli, Jr.", "relation": "knows of", "confidence": 0.9, "evidence": "I thought somewhere along the line a wrote a lot of pop songs and I thought maybe there was a chance along the way there was going to be some pop music in my future, of performing my own songs and being Billy Joel or James Taylor.", "doc_title": "John Pizzarelli, Jr. interviewed by Monk Rowe, New York City, New York, January 29, 2000 [interview 1 of 2]", "collection": "hamilton", "url": "https://litsdigital.hamilton.edu/collections/object/john-pizzarelli-jr-interviewed-monk-rowe-new-york-city-new-york-january-29-2000"}]}